Cisco, Arista Trade Barbs After US Product Import Ban Upheld







byMark Haranas on July 21, 2017, 2:42 pm EDT


Printer-friendly version Email this CRN article

Pages12next ›last »The contentious legal battle between networking rivals Cisco and Arista Networks continues to rage on as the International Trade Commission (ITC) Thursday upheld its decision to ban the importation and sale of some of Arista's networking products into the United States.
Shares of Arista stock traded down more than 3 percent at $151.81 Friday afternoon after the ITC denied the vendor's request to lift the ban.
